MALACAÑANG MANILA

PRESIDENTIAL ROCLAMATION NO. 332

EXCLUDING FROM THE OPERATION OF PROCLAMATION NO. 81 DATED 31 AUGUST 1936 A CERTAIN PORTION OF THE LAND SITUATED IN THE BARANGAYS OF TRES CRUCES AND PUNTA, MUNICIPALITY OF TANZA, PROVINCE OF CAVITE, AND DECLARE THE SAME NO LONGER NECESSARY FOR PUBLIC USE OR SERVICE AND ARE OPEN FOR ALIENATION AND DISPOSITION FOR THE AFP OFF-BASE HOUSING PROGRAM TO BE DISPOSED OF UNDER THE PROVISIONS OF REPUBLIC ACTS NOS. 274 AND 730.

Upon the recommendation of the Secretary of the Department of Environment and Natural Resources and pursuant to the authority vested in me, I, JOSEPH EJERCITO ESTRADA, President of the Philippines, do hereby exclude from the operation of Proclamation No. 81 dated August 31, 1936 reserved for military purposes, a certain parcel of public domain situated in the Barangays of Tres Cruces and Punta, Municipality of Tanza, Province of Cavite and declare the same no longer necessary for public use or service and are open for alienation and disposition for the AFP Off-Base Housing Program, subject to private rights, if there be any, and actual survey, to be disposed of under the provisions of Republic Acts Nos. 274 and 730 in relation to the provisions of Public Land Act, which portions is more particularly described as follows:

Bounded on the North, by Lot 2058 A on the northeast, by Lot 2059-C; on the southeast, by Lot No. 2067; and on the west and southwest by Lots 2422 and 2064.

